Refactored the content-type test modules to a consistent fixture-driven shape: each module exposes a `portal_type` fixture (replacing the `PORTAL_TYPE`/`PERMISSION_ADD` constants), permission assertions go through the shared `permission_add` fixture, and every type gets a `test_type_in_navigation` check against `plone.displayed_types`. Also fixed a bug where `permission_add(portal_type)` was being called as a function (the fixture already returns the composed permission string). @ericof
